Q += [
("en","ai-customer-service","Your company wants to deploy an AI chatbot for customer service. Customers should resolve simple inquiries on their own. How do you implement?","AI chatbots relieve support teams but must seamlessly escalate to human agents when needed.",O(("Implement the chatbot for simple inquiries with clear escalation paths to human agents for complex issues.","Perfect! AI for routine tasks plus human escalation provides the best overall customer experience."),("Skip the chatbot entirely and maintain exclusively human support for all customer inquiries regardless.","Possible, but with high inquiry volumes the support team becomes overwhelmed and wait times increase."),("Replace the entire human support team with the AI chatbot to maximize immediate cost savings.","Dangerous! Complex problems require human empathy, creativity, and nuanced problem-solving skills.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","A customer threatens legal action in a support chat. The AI chatbot fails to recognize the escalation and responds with standard answers.","AI must recognize escalation patterns — without human takeover, situations become legally critical fast.",O(("Configure escalation rules for keywords like lawyer and lawsuit with immediate routing to human agents.","Correct! Automatic escalation on critical keywords protects against serious legal risks proactively."),("Trust that the chatbot will eventually learn to recognize these situations through machine learning alone.","Risky! Without explicit rules, the chatbot may mishandle critical situations for months continuously."),("Deactivate the chatbot for all customer communication because it cannot handle any difficult cases.","Excessive! The chatbot works well for routine inquiries — only the escalation logic needs adjustment.")),3),
("en","ai-customer-service","Your AI chatbot gives a customer an incorrect product recommendation, leading to a return and formal complaint. How do you handle this?","AI errors happen — fast correction and transparency strengthen customer trust in the long term.",O(("Apologize to the customer, correct the recommendation logic, and review similar cases systematically.","Perfect! Quick apology plus system correction builds lasting customer trust and improves service."),("Ignore the individual case because AI systems will always have some inherent error rate regardless.","Unprofessional! Every customer complaint is an opportunity to improve both the system and service."),("Permanently deactivate all AI product recommendations because they are obviously unreliable and useless.","Excessive! A single error does not justify shutting down an otherwise useful and helpful system.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","Customers complain your AI chatbot always gives the same standard responses without addressing individual problems. What do you do?","Customer satisfaction requires personalization — AI must respond contextually, not with generic answers.",O(("Improve the chatbot with context-aware responses and always enable the option for live human assistance.","Correct! Context-aware responses plus human availability significantly increases customer satisfaction."),("Replace the chatbot completely with a larger human support team to handle every single customer inquiry.","Expensive and unnecessary — with proper configuration, the chatbot can respond much more individually."),("Add even more standard response templates hoping that eventually one will match the customer question.","Counterproductive! More generic responses make the problem worse instead of solving it effectively.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","Your support team is overwhelmed with tickets. AI could automatically categorize and prioritize them. How do you introduce this system?","AI ticket categorization saves enormous time — but the criteria must be clearly defined beforehand.",O(("Define clear categories and priority rules, train the AI accordingly, and monitor accuracy continuously.","Perfect! Clear rules plus AI training plus monitoring creates an efficient ticket system for everyone."),("Let the support team continue manually categorizing and prioritizing all tickets exactly as before.","Inefficient! With growing volume, manual sorting becomes a bottleneck delaying customer responses."),("Activate AI categorization immediately for all tickets without prior rule definition or testing.","Risky! Without clear rules, AI miscategorizes tickets and urgent issues get buried and forgotten.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","A customer asks the AI chatbot for a refund. The chatbot has no authority to approve refunds. What should it do in this situation?","AI must know its limitations and transparently communicate when a human needs to take over immediately.",O(("The chatbot transparently explains its limitations and immediately routes the customer to a human agent.","Correct! Transparency about AI limitations plus quick routing builds lasting customer trust."),("The chatbot tries to distract the customer with discount codes and alternatives to avoid the refund.","Problematic! Customers see through deflection tactics and become even more dissatisfied and frustrated."),("The chatbot approves the refund independently to quickly satisfy the customer without human involvement.","Dangerous! Unauthorized refunds by AI cause significant financial and serious legal problems.")),1),
("en","ai-customer-service","You analyze customer feedback with AI and discover many customers complain about long wait times. How do you use this insight?","AI analysis of customer feedback is valuable — but only when insights lead to concrete measurable actions.",O(("Present the analysis to leadership with concrete improvement proposals and measurable target metrics.","Perfect! Data-driven analysis plus concrete action plans convinces management to make improvements."),("Archive the analysis because long wait times are a known problem that nobody can realistically solve.","Resignation! AI analyses are only valuable when they drive concrete actionable improvement measures."),("Modify chatbot responses to downplay wait times rather than actually working to reduce them.","Deceptive! Customers notice when wait times are misrepresented and completely lose all trust.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","Your AI system detects a customer is emotionally distressed. Should the AI respond empathetically or immediately transfer to a human?","Emotional situations need real humans — AI can simulate empathy but cannot genuinely feel it.",O(("The AI responds empathetically while simultaneously proactively routing to a human agent for support.","Correct! Empathetic bridging plus human handover is the best strategy for emotional situations."),("The AI transfers immediately without any response, even if a human agent is not currently available.","Problematic! Silent transfers unsettle customers — an empathetic bridging message always helps."),("The AI continues the entire conversation alone and attempts to calm the customer down independently.","Risky! Simulated empathy can backfire significantly in highly emotional customer situations.")),3),
("en","ai-customer-service","Your competitor has advanced AI customer service. Your boss demands you deploy the same system overnight. How do you respond?","AI customer service needs careful implementation — copying without strategy leads to poor quality outcomes.",O(("Explain the necessity of a structured rollout with a pilot phase and thorough quality assurance.","Perfect! Professional AI implementation takes time but delivers sustainably better results than rushing."),("Buy the same system immediately and launch it live for all customers starting today without testing.","Dangerous! Untested AI in customer service causes frustration and damages your brand reputation."),("Tell your boss that AI customer service is just hype and your manual support is completely sufficient.","Shortsighted! AI customer service is not hype — companies that fail to modernize will lose customers.")),2),
("en","ai-customer-service","A multilingual customer writes to your English AI chatbot in Spanish. The chatbot responds only in English. What is the best solution?","Multilingual AI support shows appreciation and significantly expands your potential customer base.",O(("Enable automatic language detection so the chatbot responds in the customer preferred language always.","Perfect! Automatic language detection shows customer appreciation and improves the overall experience."),("Ask the customer to repeat their inquiry in English because support is only offered in that language.","Acceptable but unfriendly — modern AI chatbots can easily handle multilingual conversations today."),("Ignore the message completely because the chatbot is not responsible for non-English language inquiries.","Unprofessional! Every customer inquiry deserves a response — language barriers are never an excuse.")),1),
]

